casebody.data:
October 17, 1949.

Per Curiam Decisions.

No. 174. Dickinson v. Porter, State Comptroller, et al. Martin M. Cooney for appellant. Robert L. Larson, Attorney General of Iowa, Don Hise, First Assistant Attorney General, Earl F. Wisdom and Bert F. Wisdom for appellees. Per Curiam:

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.

Mr. Justice Douglas took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
